                      Fun, frolic and shopping                    To ring in the spirit of the festive season, City Centre, in association with t2, hosts City Centre Puja Shopping Festival 2010, a 17-day elaborate event with loads of gifts, discounts and offers coupled with exciting activities and performances. Among the many contests on the cards, Pujoye Dujone begins today at 4 pm. In it, couples can relive the magic of togetherness with scores of fun-filled games (entry either through pre-registration or on-spot). The Best Couple will be declared at the end of a three-day competition and will finish with a high-profile fashion show. Friends Forever (September 24 - 26) will feature teams made up of friends who participate in various competitive activities. Kids Fungama (October 1 - 3), with kids corner, dancing queen/king, fancy dress, sit-and-draw, hunt for the smartest kid and more, will keep children and their parents entertained. Besides, there will be special live shows by bands Ebong Amra (September 25; 6 pm) and Bhoomi (October 3; 6 pm). The festival at New Town will also include its first anniversary celebrations.                  Event: City Centre Puja Shopping Festival 2010 hosted by City Centre, in association with t2 When: September 17 - October 3; 11 am - 7 pm Where: City Centre, Salt Lake (Kund) and New Town (Celebration Square)	                    
